Myers-Briggs Type Indicator Examples
For each of the four preferences read and understand which one of the Myers-Briggs assessment indicates your preference. Casey prefers to “Make Decisions” by
Feeling
, i.e. based primarily on values and subjective evaluations of people-centered concerns. Edward prefers to “Make Decisions by
Thinking
, i.e. based primarily on logic and on objective analysis of cause and effect.
Casey
– ENFJ
E (Extraversion) – Clarity is Moderate
: I focus on the outer world of people and activity
N (Intuition) – Clarity is Slight:
I take in information from patterns and the big picture and focus on future possibilities
F (Feeling) – Clarity is Moderate
: I make decisions based on vales and subjective evaluation of people-centered concerns
J (Judging) – Clarity is Clear:
I like a planned and organized approach, plus I want to have things settled
Edward
– INTJ
I (Introversion) – Clarity is Moderate
: I focus on the inner world of ideas and impressions
N (Intuition) – Clarity is Clear:
I take in information from patterns and the big picture and focus on future possibilities
T (Thinking) – Clarity is Moderate, almost Clear
: I make decisions based on logic and on objective analysis of cause and effect
J (Judging) – Clarity is Very Clear:
I like a planned and organized approach, plus I want to have things settled

Clarity of Report Preferences: For each of the four preferences look at how clear you were in expressing your preference for a particular pole over its opposite (i.e. your Clarity). A longer bar suggests you are quite sure about your preference, while a shorter bar suggests you are less sure about your preference. Casey and Edward both prefer to “Take in Information” from patterns and the big picture and focus on future, thus they are both
Intuitives
(N’s). But Casey only has a
Slight Clarity
with a score of 3 out of 30. In contrast Edward has a
Clear Clarity
with a score of 19 out of 30. As you can see Casey’s line is very short and Edward’s line is quite long. It is very clear that Edward is an Intuitive, while Casey is not so clear.
Meaning of Preference:

The Myers-Briggs Type doesn’t mean Casey doesn’t ever make decisions based on logic and an objective analysis of cause and effect. It just means she will normally make decisions based values and subjective evaluations of people-centered concerns. That is her natural approach to decision making. Edward is the same way. He of course can make decisions based on values and subjective evaluations of people-centered concerns. But when faced with a decision his normal approach will be based on logic and on objective analysis of cause and effect. We all use both poles of the preferences.
